author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Washington-Wilkes rallies past RMA
text:
Saturday October 10th, 2015 4:20AM Posted 8:15AM on Saturday 10th October 2015 ( 3 hours from now ) Washington-Wilkes rallies past RMA By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night VIDEO: Brown, Lanier defense spark Longhorns to tough win over GHS 
WASHINGTON — Riverside Military could not hold a slim halftime eventually falling to Washington-Wilkes 14-3 in a Region 8-AA battle on the road. 
The Eagles (1-4, 0-2 Region 8-AA) led 3-0 at halftime on the strength of a 31-yard Jordan Ainslie field goal with just over eight minutes left in the second quarter. 
The Tigers (2-4, 2-0) rallied in the second half for a pair of touchdowns to win their second straight game. 
Chandler Jones passed for 137 yards but also had one interception for Riverside. Kaseem Duke had 100 yards rushing on 15 carries and two catches for another 80 yards and Javon Thompson had three receptions 61 yards for the Eagles. 
Riverside will play host to Oglethorpe County next week. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Riverside Military Academy football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
